cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.AI

The paper deals with the analysis of evolutionary algorithms (EAs) for solving noisy optimization problems, which is a topic related to machine learning and optimization. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the analysis of noise models. Additionally, the paper uses probabilistic analysis and derives ranges of noise levels, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of the sampling strategy, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
